{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 17:33:10.979677", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of what I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"web_server_3\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"link_bandwidth_throttling\", \"sender_resource_contention\"]\n\nNotes\n- The diagnosis report indicates a host-local traffic-control (tc/netem) misconfiguration on web_server_3 causing added delay and very low TX packet counts. I mapped this to the available root-cause types \"link_bandwidth_throttling\" (to represent netem/rate-limiting/delay applied on the interface) and \"sender_resource_contention\" (to represent host-side transmit/queuing/software transmit-path issues).\n- If you want, I can refine the submission to use a single root-cause type (for example \"link_bandwidth_throttling\" alone) or pick a different available root cause label from the provided list that you prefer.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2190, "output_tokens": 186, "total_tokens": 2376, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
